#: ../../B/bboard.rst:5
msgid "bboard"
msgstr "bboard"

#: ../../B/bboard.rst:7
msgid "/bee´bord/, n\\."
msgstr "/bee´bord/, 名詞"

#: ../../B/bboard.rst:9
msgid "[contraction of ‘bulletin board’]"
msgstr "[‘bulletin board(掲示板)’の短縮]"

#: ../../B/bboard.rst:12
msgid ""
"Any electronic bulletin board; esp. used of :ref:`BBS` systems running on "
"personal micros, less frequently of a Usenet :ref:`newsgroup` (in fact, use "
"of this term for a newsgroup generally marks one either as a :ref:`newbie` "
"fresh in from the BBS world or as a real old-timer predating Usenet)."
msgstr ""
"あらゆる電子掲示板。特にパーソナルマイコン上で動く\\ :ref:`BBS`\\ システムを指す。Usenetの\\ "
":ref:`newsgroup`\\ を指すことはより少ない(実際、ニュースグループにこの用語を使うと、概してBBS世界から来たばかりの\\ "
":ref:`newbie`\\ か、Usenet以前を知る本物の古参のどちらかであることが分かる)。"

#: ../../B/bboard.rst:16
msgid ""
"At CMU and other colleges with similar facilities, refers to campus-wide "
"electronic bulletin boards."
msgstr "CMUや同様の設備を持つ他の大学では、全学的な電子掲示板を指す。"

#: ../../B/bboard.rst:19
msgid ""
"The term physical bboard is sometimes used to refer to an old-fashioned, "
"non-electronic cork-and-thumbtack memo board. At CMU, it refers to a "
"particular one outside the CS Lounge."
msgstr ""
"physical "
"bboard(物理掲示板)という用語は、コルクと画びょうの旧式の非電子的なメモ板を指すのに使われることがある。CMUでは、CSラウンジの外にある特定の一つを指す。"

#: ../../B/bboard.rst:22
msgid ""
"In either of senses 1 or 2, the term is usually prefixed by the name of the "
"intended board (‘the Moonlight Casino bboard’ or ‘market bboard’); however, "
"if the context is clear, the better-read bboards may be referred to by name "
"alone, as in (at CMU) \"Don't post for-sale ads on general\"."
msgstr ""
"語義1か2のいずれでも、この用語は通常、対象の掲示板の名前を接頭する(‘the Moonlight Casino bboard’や‘market "
"bboard’)。ただし文脈が明確なら、よく読まれている掲示板は名前だけで呼ばれることもある。たとえば(CMUで)「general(全般)に売買広告を投稿するな」のように。"
